{
  "texts": [
    "[Mal91, Ch.",
    "By the formal classification of meromorphic connections (see e.g.",
    "[Mal91, Ch.",
    "III] and the references therein), one associates to (the formalisation at ∞ of) such a connection a finite set of exponents (sometimes called exponential factors) at ∞, which are (possibly multivalued) meromorphic functions with a pole at ∞.",
    "The situation we will be considering is the case of (analytic) meromorphic connections on the Riemann sphere where both the initial connection and its Fourier transform only have one singular point, the latter being at infinity."
  ]
}